abstract="A fully integrated fast-settling Fractional-N phase-locked loop (PLL) is presented. Based on the                                                                           {\$}{\$}{\backslash}Delta {\backslash}varSigma{\$}{\$}                                                                                    $\Delta$                        $\Sigma$                                                                             modulator and I/Q generator architectures, the frequency synthesizer covers a frequency range of 130 MHz-1 GHz with a 3-KHz channel step. The constant loop bandwidth over the above tuning frequency ranges is achieved without modifying low pass filter parameters. The current of charge pump                                                                           {\$}{\$}Icp{\$}{\$}                                                                                    Icp                                                                             is programmed not only to compensate the variation of voltage-controlled oscillator gain                                                                           {\$}{\$}Kvco{\$}{\$}                                                                                    Kvco                                                                            , but also for adapting to the change of divider ratio                                                                           {\$}{\$}N{\_}{\{}m{\}}{\$}{\$}                                                                                    N                        m                                                                            . This calibration process is carried out in an open-loop condition for a small settling time. The proposed synthesizer was fabricated in 0.18 {\textmu}m CMOS process. The measurement results show that the whole synthesizer PLL draws 11.3-mA including I/Q generator from 1.8 V supply. The out-of-band phase noise is − 123 dBc